summary: Ngl (Ik this is v controversial) I always thought of phil as more feminine than dan idk why but like if they in a store and see...
question: Ngl (Ik this is v controversial) I always thought of phil as more feminine than dan idk why but like if they in a store and see a sparkly pink skirt or whatever I feel like phil would like it more than dan (not in a style way in more a feminine way) and like just his mannerisms and the way he talks and his interests seem more feminine than dan (I also think Phil paints his nails but is just too scared to show them on camera) but idk Ik it doesn’t matter I’ve just been thinking tho
answer:
Hmm, i don’t know what their personal preferences are but i think Phil’s upbringing (from what i know) would hinder such inclinations, in the scenario that he has any?

Though i think he’s very much growing out of most of his reservations from before, He’s grown up in a very traditional family with his parents directly or indirectly contributing to instilling gender rolls more often than not and Phil seems to be effected by that to some extent.

Whereas, i think Dan is more comfortable with rejecting the concept of social constructs anyway which he depicts time and time again and acknowledges publicly, like his NASA cat shirt which was supposed to be for women and applying nail polish (which Phil does not like to do and personally i don’t think this one is about gender rolls just a preference. I don’t like stuff on my nails as well, feels weird)

Phil does have mannerisms (esp in body language) which could be translated as ‘feminine’ but i think they both do and gender definition is such a silly thing to me because it tries to remove individuality which is all over the horizon from person to person regardless of gender and if you want to embrace a stereotype because it defines who you feel you are it’s wonderful but i very much dislike unsaid rules of society being used to enforce how it is appropriate or not for a certain gender to act.

I think though, Dan and Phil, both, have grown more comfortable over the years with who they are as people and have learned to be more open with how they feel and how they want to express themselves and it makes my heart very warm <3

(do send in your opinions because i’m very uneducated on this tbh)
